summary:
Inspired by this drawing of the Mars Opportunity Rover - you will be missed <3 

Consider - a space bot au in which DUM-E, U and...
body:
Inspired by this drawing of the Mars Opportunity Rover - you will be missed <3

Consider - a space bot au in which DUM-E, U and Butterfingers were space exploration robots created by a team of Tony, Rhodey, Bucky, Carol, Helen, Jane and Bruce? 

Tony dreamed of one day getting to Mars ever since he was a little boy; but once he realized that his heart would never let him, he poured his entire heart and soul into bringing these bots to life so that he could be a part of it.

DUM-E is the first bot that paves the way. He’s not the brightest one, affectionately named ‘DUM-E’ by the rover team, which was quickly adopted by the rest of the media and world. He always tripped and fell over, but thankfully, Tony and Rhodey had anticipated that to help him back up. Bruce and Jane had even made him a chargeable sun hat to keep him warm and toasty!

DUM-E had so much fun sending data back over to Bucky and Carol. Even though his Earth family was far away, DUM-E never felt alone. 

But this winter was hard for DUM-E; it was very cold and very dark, and he was getting oh so tired. Maybe it was time for him to take a nap…

“My battery is low. It’s getting dark outside.“

The team tried over and over again to coax DUM-E to wake up, but after months and months of trying, it was time to say goodbye. The rest of the world cries with them when the news is released, with letters and sketches pouring in from all parts of the world. 

Before DUM-E fell asleep, he sent one more private message for his Earth family.

“DUM-E will sleep, but that’s okay. I love you all. Goodnight.”

by AnnoraHenryston

“You. Who, or should I say, what are you!?”
“Tony! She’s just a kid!”
“Pepper, stand down.”

“Are you Loki? Prince of Asgard?”
“I’m no prince.”
“But you look like one.”
Tony doesn’t like her, Nick doesn’t need her, all she has is this handsome God who seems to actually understand her position.

summary: It’s Valentine’s Day. Traditionally Peter gets Aunt May a bunch of roses, with a card and some chocolate, just like Uncle Ben...
body:
It’s Valentine’s Day. Traditionally Peter gets Aunt May a bunch of roses, with a card and some chocolate, just like Uncle Ben used to do for her.

This year, he also writes a card for Tony, putting it in the mail. It’s a stupid thing that Peter doesn’t think much about. Aunt May always said it was the thought that counts.

Tony opens the envelope, confused at the child like drawing of Ironman and Spider-Man fighting side by side. He opens the card.

If dads were like flowers, I’d pick you.

May opening the door to 1 (one) very emotional Tony Stark who seems to be speaking in code, and 1 (one) exasperated Pepper who is holding a massive bunch of flowers.

“Tony said, good job raising a kid like Peter.” Pepper says, handing over the flowers. May nods, confused. Tony is still babbling as Pepper turns him and leads him away.

Not the weirdest Valentine’s Day May ever had, but certainly in the top 10.
